title: Public Budget Database - Budget Authority and offsetting receipts 1976-Current

title: Completed EO 12866 Regulatory Reviews by Calendar Year
description: Annual data set of draft rules reviewed by OMB under Executive Orders 12291 and 12866.  The data provide information by agency, length of review in days, and economic significance.  This data set provides annual data going back to 1981.

organizationName: Office of Management and Budget, Executive Office of the President
QualityResponsibleAgency: Office of Information and Regulatory Affairs

title: National Nanotechnology Initiative Investments by Agency and Program Component Area
description: Data represents National Nanotechnology Initiative investments by agency and program component area (PCA) from FY 2001 through FY 2010 (requested). While this data has been available as part of the NNI's annual supplements to the President's Budget, the funding data presented here is more accessible and readily available for analysis by users to assess trends and examine investment allocations over the 10-year history of the NNI. The cumulative NNI investment of nearly $12 billion in nanotechnology research and development continues to advance our understanding of the unique phenomena and processes that occur at the nanoscale and to leverage that knowledge to speed innovation in high-impact opportunity areas such as energy, security, and medicine.
keyword: National Nanotechnology Initiative, NNI, nano, nanotech, nanotechnology, nanotechnology research, nanotechnology research funding, Federal research and development budget
subagency: Office of Science and Technology Policy
organizationName: Office of Science and Technology Policy, Executive Office of the President

title: U.S. Global Change Research Program Budget Crosscut
description: U.S. Global Change Research Program budget authority for Agency activities in which the primary focus is on:Observations, research, and analysis of climatechange and its underlying causes, managing data in support of climate researchand applications, modeling and predicting climate change and its impacts at global, regional, and local scales, analyses of climate impacts, the vulnerabilityof ecosystems, human health, andsocioeconomic activity to climate, andimplications and efficacy of adaptation options, decision support tools that inform climateadaptation and mitigation.  This crosscutdoes not include activities that implementadaptation and mitigation strategies.Communication of information related to theaforementioned activities.Procurement, acquisition, and construction in support of activities mentioned above should also be included if the project primarily supports climate science.P.L. 101606 requires this program crosscut.
keyword: USGCRP,  budget, crosscut, global change, climate change, research, SGCRP, OSP
subagency: Office of Science and Technology Policy
organizationName: Office of Science and Technology Policy, Executive Office of the President
bibliographicCitation: U.S. Global Change Research Program Annual Report - Our Changing Planet FY(xy)
analysisUnit: Individual Agency Discretionary Budget Authority in million of dollars for the U.S. Global change Research Program budget crosscut
QualityResponsibleAgency: Office of Science and Technology Policy, Executive Office of the President

title: FY2010 Federal Government Greenhouse Gas Inventory by Agency
description: The comprehensive Greenhouse Gas (GHG) Emissions Inventory for the Federal Government accounts for emissions associated with Federal operations in FY 2010. Attached files provide summaries of the FY 2010 aggregate Federal Government and individual agency Scope 1,2 and 3 emissions. The inventories are broken into two data sets: one set of GHG emissions subject to reduction targets, and a separate data set of military operations, law enforcement, and other emissions not subject to reduction targets.
keyword: Greenhouse Gas, Emissions, GHG, Carbon dioxide, MTCO2e, Scope 1, Scope 2, Scope 3
organizationName: Council on Environmental Quality, Executive Office of the President
reasonBeingNew: This is the first release of FY10 GHG data collected by Federal agencies and submitted to CEQ Jan 31, 2011.
